Package: trackJR
Type: Package
Title: Using Julia language and R for tracking tiny insects
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Gerardo de la Vega
Maintainer: Gerardo de la Vega <delavega.gerardo@gmail.com>
Description: Using Julia language and R for tracking tiny insects: an analysis of microhymenoptera wasps and olfactometers responses
    This package call Julia lang for its velocity to solve a simple edgeness function in each frame of a video and save its more brightness pixel to a data frame. 
    Tiny insects such as mycrohymenoptera seem to be few pixels in a frame. So, this package could help to fastly identify the position of the insect.
    THe output is a data.frame with each video frame, x and y position. Also for batch processing you could get a list with all videos and data.frames
license: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.1)
Imports:
    JuliaCall
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
